The paper deals with approximation algorithms for the Minimum Dominating Set problem on string graphs and its subclasses. This involves studying intersection graphs of various types of paths and curves, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also introduces and studies a new problem called Stabbing segments with rays (SSR), which is a problem in computational geometry and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper uses techniques from graph theory (cs.GT) and approximation algorithms (cs.CC) to derive its results. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS and cs.CG, followed by cs.DM, cs.GT, and cs.CC.
